    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-8a-3-3-task-1">
      <statement>
        <p>
            Next, evaluate the derivatives you determined in (a) at <m>a = 0</m> and use these to find the values of the coefficients of the Taylor polynomial centered at <m>a = 0</m>.  Record your work in the blank spaces provided.
            <md>
              <mrow> k \amp= 0 \amp f(0) \amp= \frac{1}{1-0} = 1 \amp c_0 \amp= f(0) = 1</mrow>
              <mrow> k \amp= 1 \amp f'(0) \amp= \frac{(-1)}{(1-0)^{2}} \cdot (-1) = 1 \amp c_1 \amp= \frac{f'(0)}{1!} = \frac{1}{1!} = 1</mrow>
              <mrow> k \amp= <fillin characters="1" /> \amp f''(0) \amp= <fillin characters="5" /> \amp c_2 \amp= \frac{f''(0)}{2!} = <fillin characters="4" /></mrow>
              <mrow> k \amp= <fillin characters="1" /> \amp f'''(0) \amp= <fillin characters="5" /> \amp c_3 \amp= <fillin characters="9" /></mrow>
              <mrow> k \amp= <fillin characters="1" /> \amp f^{(4)}(0) \amp= <fillin characters="5" /> \amp c_4 \amp= <fillin characters="9" />   </mrow>
              <mrow> k \amp= <fillin characters="1" /> \amp f^{(5)}(0) \amp= <fillin characters="5" /> \amp c_5 \amp= <fillin characters="9" /></mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer>
